        h4.subheader Step 6. Live Prototyping
        p I decided to use 
          a(href="http://foundation.zurb.com/" title="check out Foundation 5") Foundation 5
          |  to develop a live prototype of Thengine's MVP so I could test the design at local music venues. I would arrive early to a show and ask fans to use their own devices to look at the landing page. I would ask simple questions like "What do you think this website is about?" "What does this website have to offer?" "Would you refer this to a friend or family member?".

          img(src="images/thengine-live-prototype-desktop.jpg" alt="the desktop version of my live prototype of thengine - verson 1.0" title="Thenine UX Live Prototype Desktop")
          img(src="images/thengine-live-prototype-tablet.jpg" alt="the tablet version of my live prototype of thengine - verson 1.0" title="Thenine UX Live Prototype Tablet")
          img(src="images/thengine-live-prototype-mobile.jpg" alt="the mobile version of my live prototype of thengine - verson 1.0" title="Thenine UX Live Prototype Mobile")

        h4.subheader Step 7. Interaction Design
        p I read Dan Saffer's 
          a(href="http://www.amazon.com/Microinteractions-Color-Edition-Designing-Details/dp/1491945923" title="check out Microinteractions on Amazon")
            em Microinteractions: Designing with Details
          |  and was compelled by the power of small visceral components.
        p The idea that an application could create joy for its users through its microinteractions was highly appealing to me. It wasn't just about the layout, hierarchy, color and imagery. It was about the way that the application responded to the user and sparked delight through small yet engaging responses.

        p I lent my hand at designing a custom share button for Thengine. I wanted it to 
          em feel
          |  fun and encourage users to engage with it again and again.

        p Inspired by 
          a(href="https://path.com/" title="See the homepage for Path, the app that inspired my microinteraction design for thengine") Path
          |  I designed a share icon that rotated and spun out buttons when clicked.

        .row
